145static void
146gk104_ram_train(struct gk104_ramfuc *fuc, u32 mask, u32 data)
147{
148 struct gk104_ram *ram = container_of(fuc, typeof(*ram), fuc);
149 u32 addr = 0x110974, i;
150
151 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f910, mask, data);
152 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f914, mask, data);
153
154 for (i = 0; (data & 0x80000000) && i < ram->parts; addr += 0x1000, i++) {
155 if (ram->pmask & (1 << i))
156 continue;
157 ram_wait(fuc, addr, 0x0000000f, 0x00000000, 500000);
158 }
159}

161static void
162r1373f4_init(struct gk104_ramfuc *fuc)
163{
164 struct gk104_ram *ram = container_of(fuc, typeof(*ram), fuc);
165 const u32 mcoef = ((--ram->P2 << 28) | (ram->N2 << 8) | ram->M2);
166 const u32 rcoef = (( ram->P1 << 16) | (ram->N1 << 8) | ram->M1);
167 const u32 runk0 = ram->fN1 << 16;
168 const u32 runk1 = ram->fN1;
169
170 if (ram->from == 2) {
171 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000000, 0x00001100);
172 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000000, 0x00000010);
173 } else {
174 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000000, 0x00010010);
175 }
176
177 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000003, 0x00000000);
178 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000010, 0x00000000);
179
180 /* (re)program refpll, if required */
181 if ((ram_rd32(fuc, 0x132024) & 0xffffffff) != rcoef ||
182 (ram_rd32(fuc, 0x132034) & 0x0000ffff) != runk1) {
183 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132000, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
184 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132020, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
185 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x137320, 0x00000000);
186 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132030, 0xffff0000, runk0);
187 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132034, 0x0000ffff, runk1);
188 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x132024, rcoef);
189 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132028, 0x00080000, 0x00080000);
190 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132020, 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
191 ram_wait(fuc, 0x137390, 0x00020000, 0x00020000, 64000);
192 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132028, 0x00080000, 0x00000000);
193 }
194
195 /* (re)program mempll, if required */
196 if (ram->mode == 2) {
197 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00010000, 0x00000000);
198 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132000, 0x80000000, 0x80000000);
199 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132000, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
200 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132004, 0x103fffff, mcoef);
201 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132000, 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
202 ram_wait(fuc, 0x137390, 0x00000002, 0x00000002, 64000);
203 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000000, 0x00001100);
204 } else {
205 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000000, 0x00010100);
206 }
207
208 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000000, 0x00000010);
209}

211static void
212r1373f4_fini(struct gk104_ramfuc *fuc)
213{
214 struct gk104_ram *ram = container_of(fuc, typeof(*ram), fuc);
215 struct nvkm_ram_data *next = ram->base.next;
216 u8 v0 = next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_c0;
217 u8 v1 = next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_30;
218 u32 tmp;
219
220 tmp = ram_rd32(fuc, 0x1373ec) & ~0x00030000;
221 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373ec, tmp | (v1 << 16));
222 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f0, (~ram->mode & 3), 0x00000000);
223 if (ram->mode == 2) {
224 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000003, 0x000000002);
225 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00001100, 0x000000000);
226 } else {
227 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000003, 0x000000001);
228 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00010000, 0x000000000);
229 }
230 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f800, 0x00000030, (v0 ^ v1) << 4);
231}

233static void
234gk104_ram_nuts(struct gk104_ram *ram, struct ramfuc_reg *reg,
235 u32 _mask, u32 _data, u32 _copy)
236{
237 struct nvkm_fb *fb = ram->base.fb;
238 struct ramfuc *fuc = &ram->fuc.base;
239 struct nvkm_device *device = fb->subdev.device;
240 u32 addr = 0x110000 + (reg->addr & 0xfff);
241 u32 mask = _mask | _copy;
242 u32 data = (_data & _mask) | (reg->data & _copy);
243 u32 i;
244
245 for (i = 0; i < 16; i++, addr += 0x1000) {
246 if (ram->pnuts & (1 << i)) {
247 u32 prev = nvkm_rd32(device, addr);
248 u32 next = (prev & ~mask) | data;
249 nvkm_memx_wr32(fuc->memx, addr, next);
250 }
251 }
252}
253#define ram_nuts(s,r,m,d,c) \
254 gk104_ram_nuts((s), &(s)->fuc.r_##r, (m), (d), (c))

256static int
257gk104_ram_calc_gddr5(struct gk104_ram *ram, u32 freq)
258{
259 struct gk104_ramfuc *fuc = &ram->fuc;
260 struct nvkm_ram_data *next = ram->base.next;
261 int vc = !next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_08;
262 int mv = !next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_04;
263 u32 mask, data;
264
265 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f808, 0x40000000, 0x40000000);
266 ram_block(fuc);
267 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x62c000, 0x0f0f0000);
268
269 /* MR1: turn termination on early, for some reason.. */
270 if ((ram->base.mr[1] & 0x03c) != 0x030) {
271 ram_mask(fuc, mr[1], 0x03c, ram->base.mr[1] & 0x03c);
272 ram_nuts(ram, mr[1], 0x03c, ram->base.mr1_nuts & 0x03c, 0x000);
273 }
274
275 if (vc == 1 && ram_have(fuc, gpio2E)) {
276 u32 temp = ram_mask(fuc, gpio2E, 0x3000, fuc->r_func2E[1]);
277 if (temp != ram_rd32(fuc, gpio2E)) {
278 ram_wr32(fuc, gpiotrig, 1);
279 ram_nsec(fuc, 20000);
280 }
281 }
282
283 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00000800, 0x00000000);
284
285 gk104_ram_train(fuc, 0x01020000, 0x000c0000);
286
287 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f210, 0x00000000); /* REFRESH_AUTO = 0 */
288 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
289 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f310, 0x00000001); /* REFRESH */
290 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
291
292 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x80000000, 0x80000000);
293 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f314, 0x00000001); /* PRECHARGE */
294 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x80000000, 0x00000000);
295 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f090, 0x00000061);
296 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f090, 0xc000007f);
297 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
298
299 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f698, 0x00000000);
300 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f69c, 0x00000000);
301
302 /*XXX: there does appear to be some kind of condition here, simply
303 * modifying these bits in the vbios from the default pl0
304 * entries shows no change. however, the data does appear to
305 * be correct and may be required for the transition back
306 */
307 mask = 0x800f07e0;
308 data = 0x00030000;
309 if (ram_rd32(fuc, 0x10f978) & 0x00800000)
310 data |= 0x00040000;
311
312 if (1) {
313 data |= 0x800807e0;
314 switch (next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_c0) {
315 case 3: data &= ~0x00000040; break;
316 case 2: data &= ~0x00000100; break;
317 case 1: data &= ~0x80000000; break;
318 case 0: data &= ~0x00000400; break;
319 }
320
321 switch (next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_30) {
322 case 3: data &= ~0x00000020; break;
323 case 2: data &= ~0x00000080; break;
324 case 1: data &= ~0x00080000; break;
325 case 0: data &= ~0x00000200; break;
326 }
327 }
328
329 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_80)
330 mask |= 0x03000000;
331 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_40)
332 mask |= 0x00002000;
333 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_10)
334 mask |= 0x00004000;
335 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_08)
336 mask |= 0x00000003;
337 else {
338 mask |= 0x34000000;
339 if (ram_rd32(fuc, 0x10f978) & 0x00800000)
340 mask |= 0x40000000;
341 }
342 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f824, mask, data);
343
344 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132040, 0x00010000, 0x00000000);
345
346 if (ram->from == 2 && ram->mode != 2) {
347 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f808, 0x00080000, 0x00000000);
348 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x18008000, 0x00008000);
349 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f800, 0x00000000, 0x00000004);
350 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x00008000, 0x01040010);
351 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x01000000, 0x00000000);
352 r1373f4_init(fuc);
353 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f0, 0x00000002, 0x00000001);
354 r1373f4_fini(fuc);
355 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x00c00000, 0x00240001);
356 } else
357 if (ram->from != 2 && ram->mode != 2) {
358 r1373f4_init(fuc);
359 r1373f4_fini(fuc);
360 }
361
362 if (ram_have(fuc, gpioMV)) {
363 u32 temp = ram_mask(fuc, gpioMV, 0x3000, fuc->r_funcMV[mv]);
364 if (temp != ram_rd32(fuc, gpioMV)) {
365 ram_wr32(fuc, gpiotrig, 1);
366 ram_nsec(fuc, 64000);
367 }
368 }
369
370 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_40 ||
371 next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_10) {
372 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132040, 0x00010000, 0x00010000);
373 ram_nsec(fuc, 20000);
374 }
375
376 if (ram->from != 2 && ram->mode == 2) {
377 if (0 /*XXX: Titan */)
378 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x18000000, 0x18000000);
379 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f800, 0x00000004, 0x00000000);
380 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f0, 0x00000000, 0x00000002);
381 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x00800001, 0x00408010);
382 r1373f4_init(fuc);
383 r1373f4_fini(fuc);
384 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f808, 0x00000000, 0x00080000);
385 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00808000, 0x00800000);
386 } else
387 if (ram->from == 2 && ram->mode == 2) {
388 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f800, 0x00000004, 0x00000000);
389 r1373f4_init(fuc);
390 r1373f4_fini(fuc);
391 }
392
393 if (ram->mode != 2) /*XXX*/ {
394 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_40)
395 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f670, 0x80000000, 0x80000000);
396 }
397
398 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f65c, 0x00000011 * next->bios.rammap_11_11_0c);
399 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f6b8, 0x01010101 * next->bios.ramcfg_11_09);
400 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f6bc, 0x01010101 * next->bios.ramcfg_11_09);
401
402 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_08 && !next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_04) {
403 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f698, 0x01010101 * next->bios.ramcfg_11_04);
404 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f69c, 0x01010101 * next->bios.ramcfg_11_04);
405 } else
406 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_08) {
407 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f698, 0x00000000);
408 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f69c, 0x00000000);
409 }
410
411 if (ram->mode != 2) {
412 u32 data = 0x01000100 * next->bios.ramcfg_11_04;
413 ram_nuke(fuc, 0x10f694);
414 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f694, 0xff00ff00, data);
415 }
416
417 if (ram->mode == 2 && next->bios.ramcfg_11_08_10)
418 data = 0x00000080;
419 else
420 data = 0x00000000;
421 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f60c, 0x00000080, data);
422
423 mask = 0x00070000;
424 data = 0x00000000;
425 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_80)
426 data |= 0x03000000;
427 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_40)
428 data |= 0x00002000;
429 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_10)
430 data |= 0x00004000;
431 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_08)
432 data |= 0x00000003;
433 else
434 data |= 0x74000000;
435 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f824, mask, data);
436
437 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_01_08)
438 data = 0x00000000;
439 else
440 data = 0x00001000;
441 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00001000, data);
442
443 if (ram_rd32(fuc, 0x10f670) & 0x80000000) {
444 ram_nsec(fuc, 10000);
445 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f670, 0x80000000, 0x00000000);
446 }
447
448 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_08_01)
449 data = 0x00100000;
450 else
451 data = 0x00000000;
452 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f82c, 0x00100000, data);
453
454 data = 0x00000000;
455 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_08_08)
456 data |= 0x00002000;
457 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_08_04)
458 data |= 0x00001000;
459 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_08_02)
460 data |= 0x00004000;
461 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x00007000, data);
462
463 /* PFB timing */
464 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f248, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[10]);
465 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f290, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[0]);
466 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f294, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[1]);
467 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f298, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[2]);
468 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f29c, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[3]);
469 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2a0, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[4]);
470 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2a4, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[5]);
471 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2a8, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[6]);
472 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2ac, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[7]);
473 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2cc, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[8]);
474 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2e8, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[9]);
475
476 data = mask = 0x00000000;
477 if (ram->diff.ramcfg_11_08_20) {
478 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_08_20)
479 data |= 0x01000000;
480 mask |= 0x01000000;
481 }
482 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, mask, data);
483
484 data = mask = 0x00000000;
485 if (ram->diff.ramcfg_11_02_03) {
486 data |= next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_03 << 8;
487 mask |= 0x00000300;
488 }
489 if (ram->diff.ramcfg_11_01_10) {
490 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_01_10)
491 data |= 0x70000000;
492 mask |= 0x70000000;
493 }
494 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f604, mask, data);
495
496 data = mask = 0x00000000;
497 if (ram->diff.timing_20_30_07) {
498 data |= next->bios.timing_20_30_07 << 28;
499 mask |= 0x70000000;
500 }
501 if (ram->diff.ramcfg_11_01_01) {
502 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_01_01)
503 data |= 0x00000100;
504 mask |= 0x00000100;
505 }
506 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f614, mask, data);
507
508 data = mask = 0x00000000;
509 if (ram->diff.timing_20_30_07) {
510 data |= next->bios.timing_20_30_07 << 28;
511 mask |= 0x70000000;
512 }
513 if (ram->diff.ramcfg_11_01_02) {
514 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_01_02)
515 data |= 0x00000100;
516 mask |= 0x00000100;
517 }
518 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f610, mask, data);
519
520 mask = 0x33f00000;
521 data = 0x00000000;
522 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_01_04)
523 data |= 0x20200000;
524 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_80)
525 data |= 0x12800000;
526 /*XXX: see note above about there probably being some condition
527 * for the 10f824 stuff that uses ramcfg 3...
528 */
529 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_f0) {
530 if (next->bios.rammap_11_08_0c) {
531 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_80)
532 mask |= 0x00000020;
533 else
534 data |= 0x00000020;
535 mask |= 0x00000004;
536 }
537 } else {
538 mask |= 0x40000020;
539 data |= 0x00000004;
540 }

542 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f808, mask, data);
543
544 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f870, 0x11111111 * next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_0f);
545
546 data = mask = 0x00000000;
547 if (ram->diff.ramcfg_11_02_03) {
548 data |= next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_03;
549 mask |= 0x00000003;
550 }
551 if (ram->diff.ramcfg_11_01_10) {
552 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_01_10)
553 data |= 0x00000004;
554 mask |= 0x00000004;
555 }
556
557 if ((ram_mask(fuc, 0x100770, mask, data) & mask & 4) != (data & 4)) {
558 ram_mask(fuc, 0x100750, 0x00000008, 0x00000008);
559 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x100710, 0x00000000);
560 ram_wait(fuc, 0x100710, 0x80000000, 0x80000000, 200000);
561 }
562
563 data = next->bios.timing_20_30_07 << 8;
564 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_01_01)
565 data |= 0x80000000;
566 ram_mask(fuc, 0x100778, 0x00000700, data);
567
568 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f250, 0x000003f0, next->bios.timing_20_2c_003f << 4);
569 data = (next->bios.timing[10] & 0x7f000000) >> 24;
570 if (data < next->bios.timing_20_2c_1fc0)
571 data = next->bios.timing_20_2c_1fc0;
572 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f24c, 0x7f000000, data << 24);
573 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f224, 0x001f0000, next->bios.timing_20_30_f8 << 16);
574
575 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10fec4, 0x041e0f07, next->bios.timing_20_31_0800 << 26 |
576 next->bios.timing_20_31_0780 << 17 |
577 next->bios.timing_20_31_0078 << 8 |
578 next->bios.timing_20_31_0007);
579 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10fec8, 0x00000027, next->bios.timing_20_31_8000 << 5 |
580 next->bios.timing_20_31_7000);
581
582 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f090, 0x4000007e);
583 ram_nsec(fuc, 2000);
584 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f314, 0x00000001); /* PRECHARGE */
585 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f310, 0x00000001); /* REFRESH */
586 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f210, 0x80000000); /* REFRESH_AUTO = 1 */
587
588 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_08_10 && (ram->mode == 2) /*XXX*/) {
589 u32 temp = ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f294, 0xff000000, 0x24000000);
590 gk104_ram_train(fuc, 0xbc0e0000, 0xa4010000); /*XXX*/
591 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
592 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f294, temp);
593 }
594
595 ram_mask(fuc, mr[3], 0xfff, ram->base.mr[3]);
596 ram_wr32(fuc, mr[0], ram->base.mr[0]);
597 ram_mask(fuc, mr[8], 0xfff, ram->base.mr[8]);
598 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
599 ram_mask(fuc, mr[1], 0xfff, ram->base.mr[1]);
600 ram_mask(fuc, mr[5], 0xfff, ram->base.mr[5] & ~0x004); /* LP3 later */
601 ram_mask(fuc, mr[6], 0xfff, ram->base.mr[6]);
602 ram_mask(fuc, mr[7], 0xfff, ram->base.mr[7]);
603
604 if (vc == 0 && ram_have(fuc, gpio2E)) {
605 u32 temp = ram_mask(fuc, gpio2E, 0x3000, fuc->r_func2E[0]);
606 if (temp != ram_rd32(fuc, gpio2E)) {
607 ram_wr32(fuc, gpiotrig, 1);
608 ram_nsec(fuc, 20000);
609 }
610 }
611
612 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x80000000, 0x80000000);
613 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f318, 0x00000001); /* NOP? */
614 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x80000000, 0x00000000);
615 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
616 ram_nuts(ram, 0x10f200, 0x18808800, 0x00000000, 0x18808800);
617
618 data = ram_rd32(fuc, 0x10f978);
619 data &= ~0x00046144;
620 data |= 0x0000000b;
621 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_08) {
622 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_04)
623 data |= 0x0000200c;
624 else
625 data |= 0x00000000;
626 } else {
627 data |= 0x00040044;
628 }
629 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f978, data);
630
631 if (ram->mode == 1) {
632 data = ram_rd32(fuc, 0x10f830) | 0x00000001;
633 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f830, data);
634 }
635
636 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_08) {
637 data = 0x88020000;
638 if ( next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_04)
639 data |= 0x10000000;
640 if (!next->bios.rammap_11_08_10)
641 data |= 0x00080000;
642 } else {
643 data = 0xa40e0000;
644 }
645 gk104_ram_train(fuc, 0xbc0f0000, data);
646 if (1) /* XXX: not always? */
647 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
648
649 if (ram->mode == 2) { /*XXX*/
650 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f800, 0x00000004, 0x00000004);
651 }
652
653 /* LP3 */
654 if (ram_mask(fuc, mr[5], 0x004, ram->base.mr[5]) != ram->base.mr[5])
655 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
656
657 if (ram->mode != 2) {
658 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x01000000, 0x01000000);
659 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x01000000, 0x00000000);
660 }
661
662 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_02)
663 gk104_ram_train(fuc, 0x80020000, 0x01000000);
664
665 ram_unblock(fuc);
666 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x62c000, 0x0f0f0f00);
667
668 if (next->bios.rammap_11_08_01)
669 data = 0x00000800;
670 else
671 data = 0x00000000;
672 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00000800, data);
673 ram_nuts(ram, 0x10f200, 0x18808800, data, 0x18808800);
674 return 0;
675}

700static int
701gk104_ram_calc_sddr3(struct gk104_ram *ram, u32 freq)
702{
703 struct gk104_ramfuc *fuc = &ram->fuc;
704 const u32 rcoef = (( ram->P1 << 16) | (ram->N1 << 8) | ram->M1);
705 const u32 runk0 = ram->fN1 << 16;
706 const u32 runk1 = ram->fN1;
707 struct nvkm_ram_data *next = ram->base.next;
708 int vc = !next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_08;
709 int mv = !next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_04;
710 u32 mask, data;
711
712 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f808, 0x40000000, 0x40000000);
713 ram_block(fuc);
714 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x62c000, 0x0f0f0000);
715
716 if (vc == 1 && ram_have(fuc, gpio2E)) {
717 u32 temp = ram_mask(fuc, gpio2E, 0x3000, fuc->r_func2E[1]);
718 if (temp != ram_rd32(fuc, gpio2E)) {
719 ram_wr32(fuc, gpiotrig, 1);
720 ram_nsec(fuc, 20000);
721 }
722 }
723
724 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00000800, 0x00000000);
725 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_f0)
726 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f808, 0x04000000, 0x04000000);
727
728 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f314, 0x00000001); /* PRECHARGE */
729
730 if (next->bios.ramcfg_DLLoff)
731 nvkm_sddr3_dll_disable(fuc);
732
733 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f210, 0x00000000); /* REFRESH_AUTO = 0 */
734 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f310, 0x00000001); /* REFRESH */
735 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x80000000, 0x80000000);
736 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f310, 0x00000001); /* REFRESH */
737 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x80000000, 0x00000000);
738 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
739
740 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f090, 0x00000060);
741 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f090, 0xc000007e);
742
743 /*XXX: there does appear to be some kind of condition here, simply
744 * modifying these bits in the vbios from the default pl0
745 * entries shows no change. however, the data does appear to
746 * be correct and may be required for the transition back
747 */
748 mask = 0x00010000;
749 data = 0x00010000;
750
751 if (1) {
752 mask |= 0x800807e0;
753 data |= 0x800807e0;
754 switch (next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_c0) {
755 case 3: data &= ~0x00000040; break;
756 case 2: data &= ~0x00000100; break;
757 case 1: data &= ~0x80000000; break;
758 case 0: data &= ~0x00000400; break;
759 }
760
761 switch (next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_30) {
762 case 3: data &= ~0x00000020; break;
763 case 2: data &= ~0x00000080; break;
764 case 1: data &= ~0x00080000; break;
765 case 0: data &= ~0x00000200; break;
766 }
767 }
768
769 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_80)
770 mask |= 0x03000000;
771 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_40)
772 mask |= 0x00002000;
773 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_10)
774 mask |= 0x00004000;
775 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_08)
776 mask |= 0x00000003;
777 else
778 mask |= 0x14000000;
779 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f824, mask, data);
780
781 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132040, 0x00010000, 0x00000000);
782
783 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000000, 0x00010010);
784 data = ram_rd32(fuc, 0x1373ec) & ~0x00030000;
785 data |= next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_30 << 16;
786 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x1373ec, data);
787 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000003, 0x00000000);
788 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000010, 0x00000000);
789
790 /* (re)program refpll, if required */
791 if ((ram_rd32(fuc, 0x132024) & 0xffffffff) != rcoef ||
792 (ram_rd32(fuc, 0x132034) & 0x0000ffff) != runk1) {
793 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132000, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
794 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132020, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
795 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x137320, 0x00000000);
796 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132030, 0xffff0000, runk0);
797 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132034, 0x0000ffff, runk1);
798 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x132024, rcoef);
799 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132028, 0x00080000, 0x00080000);
800 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132020, 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
801 ram_wait(fuc, 0x137390, 0x00020000, 0x00020000, 64000);
802 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132028, 0x00080000, 0x00000000);
803 }
804
805 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000010, 0x00000010);
806 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00000003, 0x00000001);
807 ram_mask(fuc, 0x1373f4, 0x00010000, 0x00000000);
808
809 if (ram_have(fuc, gpioMV)) {
810 u32 temp = ram_mask(fuc, gpioMV, 0x3000, fuc->r_funcMV[mv]);
811 if (temp != ram_rd32(fuc, gpioMV)) {
812 ram_wr32(fuc, gpiotrig, 1);
813 ram_nsec(fuc, 64000);
814 }
815 }
816
817 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_40 ||
818 next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_10) {
819 ram_mask(fuc, 0x132040, 0x00010000, 0x00010000);
820 ram_nsec(fuc, 20000);
821 }
822
823 if (ram->mode != 2) /*XXX*/ {
824 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_40)
825 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f670, 0x80000000, 0x80000000);
826 }
827
828 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f65c, 0x00000011 * next->bios.rammap_11_11_0c);
829 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f6b8, 0x01010101 * next->bios.ramcfg_11_09);
830 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f6bc, 0x01010101 * next->bios.ramcfg_11_09);
831
832 mask = 0x00010000;
833 data = 0x00000000;
834 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_80)
835 data |= 0x03000000;
836 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_02_40)
837 data |= 0x00002000;
838 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_10)
839 data |= 0x00004000;
840 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_08)
841 data |= 0x00000003;
842 else
843 data |= 0x14000000;
844 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f824, mask, data);
845 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
846
847 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_08_01)
848 data = 0x00100000;
849 else
850 data = 0x00000000;
851 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f82c, 0x00100000, data);
852
853 /* PFB timing */
854 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f248, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[10]);
855 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f290, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[0]);
856 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f294, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[1]);
857 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f298, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[2]);
858 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f29c, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[3]);
859 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2a0, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[4]);
860 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2a4, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[5]);
861 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2a8, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[6]);
862 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2ac, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[7]);
863 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2cc, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[8]);
864 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f2e8, 0xffffffff, next->bios.timing[9]);
865
866 mask = 0x33f00000;
867 data = 0x00000000;
868 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_01_04)
869 data |= 0x20200000;
870 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_80)
871 data |= 0x12800000;
872 /*XXX: see note above about there probably being some condition
873 * for the 10f824 stuff that uses ramcfg 3...
874 */
875 if (next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_f0) {
876 if (next->bios.rammap_11_08_0c) {
877 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_11_07_80)
878 mask |= 0x00000020;
879 else
880 data |= 0x00000020;
881 mask |= 0x08000004;
882 }
883 data |= 0x04000000;
884 } else {
885 mask |= 0x44000020;
886 data |= 0x08000004;
887 }
888
889 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f808, mask, data);
890
891 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f870, 0x11111111 * next->bios.ramcfg_11_03_0f);
892
893 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f250, 0x000003f0, next->bios.timing_20_2c_003f << 4);
894
895 data = (next->bios.timing[10] & 0x7f000000) >> 24;
896 if (data < next->bios.timing_20_2c_1fc0)
897 data = next->bios.timing_20_2c_1fc0;
898 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f24c, 0x7f000000, data << 24);
899
900 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f224, 0x001f0000, next->bios.timing_20_30_f8 << 16);
901
902 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f090, 0x4000007f);
903 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
904
905 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f314, 0x00000001); /* PRECHARGE */
906 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f310, 0x00000001); /* REFRESH */
907 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f210, 0x80000000); /* REFRESH_AUTO = 1 */
908 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
909
910 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_DLLoff) {
911 ram_mask(fuc, mr[1], 0x1, 0x0);
912 nvkm_sddr3_dll_reset(fuc);
913 }
914
915 ram_mask(fuc, mr[2], 0x00000fff, ram->base.mr[2]);
916 ram_mask(fuc, mr[1], 0xffffffff, ram->base.mr[1]);
917 ram_wr32(fuc, mr[0], ram->base.mr[0]);
918 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
919
920 if (!next->bios.ramcfg_DLLoff) {
921 nvkm_sddr3_dll_reset(fuc);
922 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
923 }
924
925 if (vc == 0 && ram_have(fuc, gpio2E)) {
926 u32 temp = ram_mask(fuc, gpio2E, 0x3000, fuc->r_func2E[0]);
927 if (temp != ram_rd32(fuc, gpio2E)) {
928 ram_wr32(fuc, gpiotrig, 1);
929 ram_nsec(fuc, 20000);
930 }
931 }
932
933 if (ram->mode != 2) {
934 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x01000000, 0x01000000);
935 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f830, 0x01000000, 0x00000000);
936 }
937
938 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x80000000, 0x80000000);
939 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x10f318, 0x00000001); /* NOP? */
940 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x80000000, 0x00000000);
941 ram_nsec(fuc, 1000);
942
943 ram_unblock(fuc);
944 ram_wr32(fuc, 0x62c000, 0x0f0f0f00);
945
946 if (next->bios.rammap_11_08_01)
947 data = 0x00000800;
948 else
949 data = 0x00000000;
950 ram_mask(fuc, 0x10f200, 0x00000800, data);
951 return 0;
952}

956 ******************************************************************************/

958static int
959gk104_ram_calc_data(struct gk104_ram *ram, u32 khz, struct nvkm_ram_data *data)
960{
961 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &ram->base.fb->subdev;
962 struct nvkm_ram_data *cfg;
963 u32 mhz = khz / 1000;
964
965 list_for_each_entry(cfg, &ram->cfg, head) {
966 if (mhz >= cfg->bios.rammap_min &&
967 mhz <= cfg->bios.rammap_max) {
968 *data = *cfg;
969 data->freq = khz;
970 return 0;
971 }
972 }
973
974 nvkm_error(subdev, "ramcfg data for %dMHz not found\n", mhz);
975 return -EINVAL;
976}
977
978static int
979gk104_calc_pll_output(int fN, int M, int N, int P, int clk)
980{
981 return ((clk * N) + (((u16)(fN + 4096) * clk) >> 13)) / (M * P);
982}
983
984static int
985gk104_pll_calc_hiclk(int target_khz, int crystal,
986 int *N1, int *fN1, int *M1, int *P1,
987 int *N2, int *M2, int *P2)
988{
989 int best_clk __unused = 0, best_err = target_khz, p_ref, n_ref;
990 bool upper = false;
991
992 *M1 = 1;
993 /* M has to be 1, otherwise it gets unstable */
994 *M2 = 1;
995 /* can be 1 or 2, sticking with 1 for simplicity */
996 *P2 = 1;
997
998 for (p_ref = 0x7; p_ref >= 0x5; --p_ref) {
999 for (n_ref = 0x25; n_ref <= 0x2b; ++n_ref) {
1000 int cur_N, cur_clk, cur_err;
1001
1002 cur_clk = gk104_calc_pll_output(0, 1, n_ref, p_ref, crystal);
1003 cur_N = target_khz / cur_clk;
1004 cur_err = target_khz
1005 - gk104_calc_pll_output(0xf000, 1, cur_N, 1, cur_clk);
1006
1007 /* we found a better combination */
1008 if (cur_err < best_err) {
1009 best_err = cur_err;
1010 best_clk = cur_clk;
1011 *N2 = cur_N;
1012 *N1 = n_ref;
1013 *P1 = p_ref;
1014 upper = false;
1015 }
1016
1017 cur_N += 1;
1018 cur_err = gk104_calc_pll_output(0xf000, 1, cur_N, 1, cur_clk)
1019 - target_khz;
1020 if (cur_err < best_err) {
1021 best_err = cur_err;
1022 best_clk = cur_clk;
1023 *N2 = cur_N;
1024 *N1 = n_ref;
1025 *P1 = p_ref;
1026 upper = true;
1027 }
1028 }
1029 }
1030
1031 /* adjust fN to get closer to the target clock */
1032 *fN1 = (u16)((((best_err / *N2 * *P2) * (*P1 * *M1)) << 13) / crystal);
1033 if (upper)
1034 *fN1 = (u16)(1 - *fN1);
1035
1036 return gk104_calc_pll_output(*fN1, 1, *N1, *P1, crystal);
1037}
1038
1039static int
1040gk104_ram_calc_xits(struct gk104_ram *ram, struct nvkm_ram_data *next)
1041{
1042 struct gk104_ramfuc *fuc = &ram->fuc;
1043 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &ram->base.fb->subdev;
1044 int refclk, i;
1045 int ret;
1046
1047 ret = ram_init(fuc, ram->base.fb);
1048 if (ret)
1049 return ret;
1050
1051 ram->mode = (next->freq > fuc->refpll.vco1.max_freq) ? 2 : 1;
1052 ram->from = ram_rd32(fuc, 0x1373f4) & 0x0000000f;
1053
1054 /* XXX: this is *not* what nvidia do. on fermi nvidia generally
1055 * select, based on some unknown condition, one of the two possible
1056 * reference frequencies listed in the vbios table for mempll and
1057 * program refpll to that frequency.
1058 *
1059 * so far, i've seen very weird values being chosen by nvidia on
1060 * kepler boards, no idea how/why they're chosen.
1061 */
1062 refclk = next->freq;
1063 if (ram->mode == 2) {
1064 ret = gk104_pll_calc_hiclk(next->freq, subdev->device->crystal,
1065 &ram->N1, &ram->fN1, &ram->M1, &ram->P1,
1066 &ram->N2, &ram->M2, &ram->P2);
1067 fuc->mempll.refclk = ret;
1068 if (ret <= 0) {
1069 nvkm_error(subdev, "unable to calc plls\n");
1070 return -EINVAL;
1071 }
1072 nvkm_debug(subdev, "sucessfully calced PLLs for clock %i kHz"
1073 " (refclock: %i kHz)\n", next->freq, ret);
1074 } else {
1075 /* calculate refpll coefficients */
1076 ret = gt215_pll_calc(subdev, &fuc->refpll, refclk, &ram->N1,
1077 &ram->fN1, &ram->M1, &ram->P1);
1078 fuc->mempll.refclk = ret;
1079 if (ret <= 0) {
1080 nvkm_error(subdev, "unable to calc refpll\n");
1081 return -EINVAL;
1082 }
1083 }
1084
1085 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(fuc->r_mr); i++) {
1086 if (ram_have(fuc, mr[i]))
1087 ram->base.mr[i] = ram_rd32(fuc, mr[i]);
1088 }
1089 ram->base.freq = next->freq;
1090
1091 switch (ram->base.type) {
1092 case NVKM_RAM_TYPE_DDR3:
1093 ret = nvkm_sddr3_calc(&ram->base);
1094 if (ret == 0)
1095 ret = gk104_ram_calc_sddr3(ram, next->freq);
1096 break;
1097 case NVKM_RAM_TYPE_GDDR5:
1098 ret = nvkm_gddr5_calc(&ram->base, ram->pnuts != 0);
1099 if (ret == 0)
1100 ret = gk104_ram_calc_gddr5(ram, next->freq);
1101 break;
1102 default:
1103 ret = -ENOSYS;
1104 break;
1105 }
1106
1107 return ret;
1108}
1109
1110static int
1111gk104_ram_calc(struct nvkm_ram *base, u32 freq)
1112{
1113 struct gk104_ram *ram = gk104_ram(base);
1114 struct nvkm_clk *clk = ram->base.fb->subdev.device->clk;
1115 struct nvkm_ram_data *xits = &ram->base.xition;
1116 struct nvkm_ram_data *copy;
1117 int ret;
1118
1119 if (ram->base.next == NULL) {
1120 ret = gk104_ram_calc_data(ram,
1121 nvkm_clk_read(clk, nv_clk_src_mem),
1122 &ram->base.former);
1123 if (ret)
1124 return ret;
1125
1126 ret = gk104_ram_calc_data(ram, freq, &ram->base.target);
1127 if (ret)
1128 return ret;
1129
1130 if (ram->base.target.freq < ram->base.former.freq) {
1131 *xits = ram->base.target;
1132 copy = &ram->base.former;
1133 } else {
1134 *xits = ram->base.former;
1135 copy = &ram->base.target;
1136 }
1137
1138 xits->bios.ramcfg_11_02_04 = copy->bios.ramcfg_11_02_04;
1139 xits->bios.ramcfg_11_02_03 = copy->bios.ramcfg_11_02_03;
1140 xits->bios.timing_20_30_07 = copy->bios.timing_20_30_07;
1141
1142 ram->base.next = &ram->base.target;
1143 if (memcmp(xits, &ram->base.former, sizeof(xits->bios)))
1144 ram->base.next = &ram->base.xition;
1145 } else {
1146 BUG_ON(ram->base.next != &ram->base.xition);
1147 ram->base.next = &ram->base.target;
1148 }
1149
1150 return gk104_ram_calc_xits(ram, ram->base.next);
1151}

1153static void
1154gk104_ram_prog_0(struct gk104_ram *ram, u32 freq)
1155{
1156 struct nvkm_device *device = ram->base.fb->subdev.device;
1157 struct nvkm_ram_data *cfg;
1158 u32 mhz = freq / 1000;
1159 u32 mask, data;
1160
1161 list_for_each_entry(cfg, &ram->cfg, head) {
1162 if (mhz >= cfg->bios.rammap_min &&
1163 mhz <= cfg->bios.rammap_max)
1164 break;
1165 }
1166
1167 if (&cfg->head == &ram->cfg)
1168 return;
1169
1170 if (mask = 0, data = 0, ram->diff.rammap_11_0a_03fe) {
1171 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_0a_03fe << 12;
1172 mask |= 0x001ff000;
1173 }
1174 if (ram->diff.rammap_11_09_01ff) {
1175 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_09_01ff;
1176 mask |= 0x000001ff;
1177 }
1178 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f468, mask, data);
1179
1180 if (mask = 0, data = 0, ram->diff.rammap_11_0a_0400) {
1181 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_0a_0400;
1182 mask |= 0x00000001;
1183 }
1184 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f420, mask, data);
1185
1186 if (mask = 0, data = 0, ram->diff.rammap_11_0a_0800) {
1187 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_0a_0800;
1188 mask |= 0x00000001;
1189 }
1190 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f430, mask, data);
1191
1192 if (mask = 0, data = 0, ram->diff.rammap_11_0b_01f0) {
1193 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_0b_01f0;
1194 mask |= 0x0000001f;
1195 }
1196 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f400, mask, data);
1197
1198 if (mask = 0, data = 0, ram->diff.rammap_11_0b_0200) {
1199 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_0b_0200 << 9;
1200 mask |= 0x00000200;
1201 }
1202 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f410, mask, data);
1203
1204 if (mask = 0, data = 0, ram->diff.rammap_11_0d) {
1205 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_0d << 16;
1206 mask |= 0x00ff0000;
1207 }
1208 if (ram->diff.rammap_11_0f) {
1209 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_0f << 8;
1210 mask |= 0x0000ff00;
1211 }
1212 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f440, mask, data);
1213
1214 if (mask = 0, data = 0, ram->diff.rammap_11_0e) {
1215 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_0e << 8;
1216 mask |= 0x0000ff00;
1217 }
1218 if (ram->diff.rammap_11_0b_0800) {
1219 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_0b_0800 << 7;
1220 mask |= 0x00000080;
1221 }
1222 if (ram->diff.rammap_11_0b_0400) {
1223 data |= cfg->bios.rammap_11_0b_0400 << 5;
1224 mask |= 0x00000020;
1225 }
1226 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f444, mask, data);
1227}

1257struct gk104_ram_train {
1258 u16 mask;
1259 struct nvbios_M0209S remap;
1260 struct nvbios_M0209S type00;
1261 struct nvbios_M0209S type01;
1262 struct nvbios_M0209S type04;
1263 struct nvbios_M0209S type06;
1264 struct nvbios_M0209S type07;
1265 struct nvbios_M0209S type08;
1266 struct nvbios_M0209S type09;
1267};
1268
1269static int
1270gk104_ram_train_type(struct nvkm_ram *ram, int i, u8 ramcfg,
1271 struct gk104_ram_train *train)
1272{
1273 struct nvkm_bios *bios = ram->fb->subdev.device->bios;
1274 struct nvbios_M0205E M0205E;
1275 struct nvbios_M0205S M0205S;
1276 struct nvbios_M0209E M0209E;
1277 struct nvbios_M0209S *remap = &train->remap;
1278 struct nvbios_M0209S *value;
1279 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
1280 u32 data;
1281
1282 /* determine type of data for this index */
1283 if (!(data = nvbios_M0205Ep(bios, i, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &M0205E)))
1284 return -ENOENT;
1285
1286 switch (M0205E.type) {
1287 case 0x00: value = &train->type00; break;
1288 case 0x01: value = &train->type01; break;
1289 case 0x04: value = &train->type04; break;
1290 case 0x06: value = &train->type06; break;
1291 case 0x07: value = &train->type07; break;
1292 case 0x08: value = &train->type08; break;
1293 case 0x09: value = &train->type09; break;
1294 default:
1295 return 0;
1296 }
1297
1298 /* training data index determined by ramcfg strap */
1299 if (!(data = nvbios_M0205Sp(bios, i, ramcfg, &ver, &hdr, &M0205S)))
1300 return -EINVAL;
1301 i = M0205S.data;
1302
1303 /* training data format information */
1304 if (!(data = nvbios_M0209Ep(bios, i, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &M0209E)))
1305 return -EINVAL;
1306
1307 /* ... and the raw data */
1308 if (!(data = nvbios_M0209Sp(bios, i, 0, &ver, &hdr, value)))
1309 return -EINVAL;
1310
1311 if (M0209E.v02_07 == 2) {
1312 /* of course! why wouldn't we have a pointer to another entry
1313 * in the same table, and use the first one as an array of
1314 * remap indices...
1315 */
1316 if (!(data = nvbios_M0209Sp(bios, M0209E.v03, 0, &ver, &hdr,
1317 remap)))
1318 return -EINVAL;
1319
1320 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(value->data); i++)
1321 value->data[i] = remap->data[value->data[i]];
1322 } else
1323 if (M0209E.v02_07 != 1)
1324 return -EINVAL;
1325
1326 train->mask |= 1 << M0205E.type;
1327 return 0;
1328}
1329
1330static int
1331gk104_ram_train_init_0(struct nvkm_ram *ram, struct gk104_ram_train *train)
1332{
1333 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &ram->fb->subdev;
1334 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
1335 int i, j;
1336
1337 if ((train->mask & 0x03d3) != 0x03d3) {
1338 nvkm_warn(subdev, "missing link training data\n");
1339 return -EINVAL;
1340 }
1341
1342 for (i = 0; i < 0x30; i++) {
1343 for (j = 0; j < 8; j += 4) {
1344 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f968 + j, 0x00000000 | (i << 8));
1345 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f920 + j, 0x00000000 |
1346 train->type08.data[i] << 4 |
1347 train->type06.data[i]);
1348 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f918 + j, train->type00.data[i]);
1349 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f920 + j, 0x00000100 |
1350 train->type09.data[i] << 4 |
1351 train->type07.data[i]);
1352 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f918 + j, train->type01.data[i]);
1353 }
1354 }
1355
1356 for (j = 0; j < 8; j += 4) {
1357 for (i = 0; i < 0x100; i++) {
1358 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f968 + j, i);
1359 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10f900 + j, train->type04.data[i]);
1360 }
1361 }
1362
1363 return 0;
1364}

1366static int
1367gk104_ram_train_init(struct nvkm_ram *ram)
1368{
1369 u8 ramcfg = nvbios_ramcfg_index(&ram->fb->subdev);
1370 struct gk104_ram_train *train;
1371 int ret, i;
1372
1373 if (!(train = kzalloc(sizeof(*train), GFP_KERNEL)))
1374 return -ENOMEM;
1375
1376 for (i = 0; i < 0x100; i++) {
1377 ret = gk104_ram_train_type(ram, i, ramcfg, train);
1378 if (ret && ret != -ENOENT)
1379 break;
1380 }
1381
1382 switch (ram->type) {
1383 case NVKM_RAM_TYPE_GDDR5:
1384 ret = gk104_ram_train_init_0(ram, train);
1385 break;
1386 default:
1387 ret = 0;
1388 break;
1389 }
1390
1391 kfree(train);
1392 return ret;
1393}
1394
1395int
1396gk104_ram_init(struct nvkm_ram *ram)
1397{
1398 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &ram->fb->subdev;
1399 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
1400 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
1401 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len, snr, ssz;
1402 u32 data, save;
1403 int i;
1404
1405 /* run a bunch of tables from rammap table. there's actually
1406 * individual pointers for each rammap entry too, but, nvidia
1407 * seem to just run the last two entries' scripts early on in
1408 * their init, and never again.. we'll just run 'em all once
1409 * for now.
1410 *
1411 * i strongly suspect that each script is for a separate mode
1412 * (likely selected by 0x10f65c's lower bits?), and the
1413 * binary driver skips the one that's already been setup by
1414 * the init tables.
1415 */
1416 data = nvbios_rammapTe(bios, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &snr, &ssz);
1417 if (!data || hdr < 0x15)
1418 return -EINVAL;
1419
1420 cnt = nvbios_rd08(bios, data + 0x14); /* guess at count */
1421 data = nvbios_rd32(bios, data + 0x10); /* guess u32... */
1422 save = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x10f65c) & 0x000000f0;
1423 for (i = 0; i < cnt; i++, data += 4) {
1424 if (i != save >> 4) {
1425 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f65c, 0x000000f0, i << 4);
1426 nvbios_exec(&(struct nvbios_init) {
1427 .subdev = subdev,
1428 .bios = bios,
1429 .offset = nvbios_rd32(bios, data),
1430 .execute = 1,
1431 });
1432 }
1433 }
1434 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f65c, 0x000000f0, save);
1435 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f584, 0x11000000, 0x00000000);
1436 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x10ecc0, 0xffffffff);
1437 nvkm_mask(device, 0x10f160, 0x00000010, 0x00000010);
1438
1439 return gk104_ram_train_init(ram);
1440}

1442static int
1443gk104_ram_ctor_data(struct gk104_ram *ram, u8 ramcfg, int i)
1444{
1445 struct nvkm_bios *bios = ram->base.fb->subdev.device->bios;
1446 struct nvkm_ram_data *cfg;
1447 struct nvbios_ramcfg *d = &ram->diff;
1448 struct nvbios_ramcfg *p, *n;
1449 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
1450 u32 data;
1451 int ret;
1452
1453 if (!(cfg = kmalloc(sizeof(*cfg), GFP_KERNEL)))
1454 return -ENOMEM;
1455 p = &list_last_entry(&ram->cfg, typeof(*cfg), head)->bios;
1456 n = &cfg->bios;
1457
1458 /* memory config data for a range of target frequencies */
1459 data = nvbios_rammapEp(bios, i, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &cfg->bios);
1460 if (ret = -ENOENT, !data)
1461 goto done;
1462 if (ret = -ENOSYS, ver != 0x11 || hdr < 0x12)
1463 goto done;
1464
1465 /* ... and a portion specific to the attached memory */
1466 data = nvbios_rammapSp(bios, data, ver, hdr, cnt, len, ramcfg,
1467 &ver, &hdr, &cfg->bios);
1468 if (ret = -EINVAL, !data)
1469 goto done;
1470 if (ret = -ENOSYS, ver != 0x11 || hdr < 0x0a)
1471 goto done;
1472
1473 /* lookup memory timings, if bios says they're present */
1474 if (cfg->bios.ramcfg_timing != 0xff) {
1475 data = nvbios_timingEp(bios, cfg->bios.ramcfg_timing,
1476 &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len,
1477 &cfg->bios);
1478 if (ret = -EINVAL, !data)
1479 goto done;
1480 if (ret = -ENOSYS, ver != 0x20 || hdr < 0x33)
1481 goto done;
1482 }
1483
1484 list_add_tail(&cfg->head, &ram->cfg);
1485 if (ret = 0, i == 0)
1486 goto done;
1487
1488 d->rammap_11_0a_03fe |= p->rammap_11_0a_03fe != n->rammap_11_0a_03fe;
1489 d->rammap_11_09_01ff |= p->rammap_11_09_01ff != n->rammap_11_09_01ff;
1490 d->rammap_11_0a_0400 |= p->rammap_11_0a_0400 != n->rammap_11_0a_0400;
1491 d->rammap_11_0a_0800 |= p->rammap_11_0a_0800 != n->rammap_11_0a_0800;
1492 d->rammap_11_0b_01f0 |= p->rammap_11_0b_01f0 != n->rammap_11_0b_01f0;
1493 d->rammap_11_0b_0200 |= p->rammap_11_0b_0200 != n->rammap_11_0b_0200;
1494 d->rammap_11_0d |= p->rammap_11_0d != n->rammap_11_0d;
1495 d->rammap_11_0f |= p->rammap_11_0f != n->rammap_11_0f;
1496 d->rammap_11_0e |= p->rammap_11_0e != n->rammap_11_0e;
1497 d->rammap_11_0b_0800 |= p->rammap_11_0b_0800 != n->rammap_11_0b_0800;
1498 d->rammap_11_0b_0400 |= p->rammap_11_0b_0400 != n->rammap_11_0b_0400;
1499 d->ramcfg_11_01_01 |= p->ramcfg_11_01_01 != n->ramcfg_11_01_01;
1500 d->ramcfg_11_01_02 |= p->ramcfg_11_01_02 != n->ramcfg_11_01_02;
1501 d->ramcfg_11_01_10 |= p->ramcfg_11_01_10 != n->ramcfg_11_01_10;
1502 d->ramcfg_11_02_03 |= p->ramcfg_11_02_03 != n->ramcfg_11_02_03;
1503 d->ramcfg_11_08_20 |= p->ramcfg_11_08_20 != n->ramcfg_11_08_20;
1504 d->timing_20_30_07 |= p->timing_20_30_07 != n->timing_20_30_07;
1505done:
1506 if (ret)
1507 kfree(cfg);
1508 return ret;
1509}

1534
1535int
1536gk104_ram_new(struct nvkm_fb *fb, struct nvkm_ram **pram)
1537{
1538 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fb->subdev;
1539 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
1540 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
1541 struct nvkm_gpio *gpio = device->gpio;
1542 struct dcb_gpio_func func;
1543 struct gk104_ram *ram;
1544 int ret, i;
1545 u8 ramcfg = nvbios_ramcfg_index(subdev);
1546 u32 tmp;
1547
1548 if (!(ram = kzalloc(sizeof(*ram), GFP_KERNEL)))
1549 return -ENOMEM;
1550 *pram = &ram->base;
1551
1552 ret = gf100_ram_ctor(&gk104_ram_func, fb, 0x022554, &ram->base);
1553 if (ret)
1554 return ret;
1555
1556 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&ram->cfg);
1557
1558 /* calculate a mask of differently configured memory partitions,
1559 * because, of course reclocking wasn't complicated enough
1560 * already without having to treat some of them differently to
1561 * the others....
1562 */
1563 ram->parts = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x022438);
1564 ram->pmask = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x022554);
1565 ram->pnuts = 0;
1566 for (i = 0, tmp = 0; i < ram->parts; i++) {
1567 if (!(ram->pmask & (1 << i))) {
1568 u32 cfg1 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x110204 + (i * 0x1000));
1569 if (tmp && tmp != cfg1) {
1570 ram->pnuts |= (1 << i);
1571 continue;
1572 }
1573 tmp = cfg1;
1574 }
1575 }
1576
1577 /* parse bios data for all rammap table entries up-front, and
1578 * build information on whether certain fields differ between
1579 * any of the entries.
1580 *
1581 * the binary driver appears to completely ignore some fields
1582 * when all entries contain the same value. at first, it was
1583 * hoped that these were mere optimisations and the bios init
1584 * tables had configured as per the values here, but there is
1585 * evidence now to suggest that this isn't the case and we do
1586 * need to treat this condition as a "don't touch" indicator.
1587 */
1588 for (i = 0; !ret; i++) {
1589 ret = gk104_ram_ctor_data(ram, ramcfg, i);
1590 if (ret && ret != -ENOENT) {
1591 nvkm_error(subdev, "failed to parse ramcfg data\n");
1592 return ret;
1593 }
1594 }
1595
1596 /* parse bios data for both pll's */
1597 ret = nvbios_pll_parse(bios, 0x0c, &ram->fuc.refpll);
1598 if (ret) {
1599 nvkm_error(subdev, "mclk refpll data not found\n");
1600 return ret;
1601 }
1602
1603 ret = nvbios_pll_parse(bios, 0x04, &ram->fuc.mempll);
1604 if (ret) {
1605 nvkm_error(subdev, "mclk pll data not found\n");
1606 return ret;
1607 }
1608
1609 /* lookup memory voltage gpios */
1610 ret = nvkm_gpio_find(gpio, 0, 0x18, DCB_GPIO_UNUSED, &func);
1611 if (ret == 0) {
1612 ram->fuc.r_gpioMV = ramfuc_reg(0x00d610 + (func.line * 0x04));
1613 ram->fuc.r_funcMV[0] = (func.log[0] ^ 2) << 12;
1614 ram->fuc.r_funcMV[1] = (func.log[1] ^ 2) << 12;
1615 }
1616
1617 ret = nvkm_gpio_find(gpio, 0, 0x2e, DCB_GPIO_UNUSED, &func);
1618 if (ret == 0) {
1619 ram->fuc.r_gpio2E = ramfuc_reg(0x00d610 + (func.line * 0x04));
1620 ram->fuc.r_func2E[0] = (func.log[0] ^ 2) << 12;
1621 ram->fuc.r_func2E[1] = (func.log[1] ^ 2) << 12;
1622 }
1623
1624 ram->fuc.r_gpiotrig = ramfuc_reg(0x00d604);
1625
1626 ram->fuc.r_0x132020 = ramfuc_reg(0x132020);
1627 ram->fuc.r_0x132028 = ramfuc_reg(0x132028);
1628 ram->fuc.r_0x132024 = ramfuc_reg(0x132024);
